<subSubSection id="C30A949AFFFD647A47D62AD8FA03FCB3" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="32" type="key">
<keyStep id="30E4DFB4FFFD647A47D62AD8FA03FEAB" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFD647A47D62AD8FA03FF33" blockId="2.[151,1436,1960,2026]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFD647A47D62AD8FA03FF33" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
1. Ligula prominent and distinctly longer than paraglossae (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFD647B442B2AD8FC25F843" box="[874,947,1960,1986]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,876,1146]" captionTargetId="figure-497@3.[151,1436,870,1165]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Mentum (ventral view): 2 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 3 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 4 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 5 Schuelea drumonti. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108348/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); post-orbital surface area (gena) densely setose, with more than 40 setae and without tubercles; maxillary palpomere 4 shorter than 3; TLA = 24.5– 27.5 (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A464B2DE8FEC9FF33" box="[266,351,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1306,1330]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,770,1265]" captionTargetId="figure-264@10.[151,1436,764,1282]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Habitus: 23 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.(Holotype); 24 Pogonoglossus giganteus (Holotype); 25 Schuelea drumonti (Holotype); 26 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus (Lectotype). Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108360/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) ............................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFFC647A43D52DE8FA03FF33" authority="Westwood." authorityName="Westwood." box="[1172,1429,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Helluodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A43D52DE8FA9DFF30" box="[1172,1291,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Helluodes</emphasis>
Westwood.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFC647A47D62DB0FA03FEAB" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFC647A47D62DB0FA03FEAB" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
- Ligula truncate and distinctly shorter than paraglossae (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A44C22DB0FC6AFF5B" box="[899,1020,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,876,1146]" captionTargetId="figure-497@3.[151,1436,870,1165]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Mentum (ventral view): 2 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 3 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 4 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 5 Schuelea drumonti. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Figs. 3–5</figureCitation>
); post-orbital surface area (gena) sparsely setose with less than 10 setae and with or without tubercles; maxillary palpomere 4 longer than 3; TLA = 19.5 ................................................................................................................................................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E4DFB4FFFC647A47D62C48FA02FE73" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFC647A47D62C48FA03FE23" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFC647A47D62C48FA03FE23" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
2. Mentum with bifid median tooth; ligula stout and of uniform width from base to apex (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A43FA2C48FA94FED3" box="[1211,1282,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,876,1146]" captionTargetId="figure-497@3.[151,1436,870,1165]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Mentum (ventral view): 2 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 3 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 4 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 5 Schuelea drumonti. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); male sternite 3 (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A464B2C10FEC9FEFB" box="[266,351,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,269,1462,1486]" captionTargetBox="[201,1408,184,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-234@8.[151,1436,160,1438]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Median depression and cluster of filamentous setae on 2nd and 3rd sternites of male: 15 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 16 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 17 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 18 2nd and 3rd sternites of female Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp. Not scaled." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) with single oval depression bearing filamentous elongated setae; TLA = 19–19.5 (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A42732C10FA11FEFB" box="[1330,1415,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1306,1330]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,770,1265]" captionTargetId="figure-264@10.[151,1436,764,1282]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Habitus: 23 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.(Holotype); 24 Pogonoglossus giganteus (Holotype); 25 Schuelea drumonti (Holotype); 26 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus (Lectotype). Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108360/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A478D2CF8FB04FE20" box="[204,1170,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">...................................................................................................................................</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFFC647A43D32CF8FA03FE23" authority="Parry." authorityName="Parry." box="[1170,1429,392,418]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Physocrotaphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A43D32CF8FAD1FE20" box="[1170,1351,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Physocrotaphus</emphasis>
Parry.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFC647A47D62CC0FA02FE73" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFC647A47D62CC0FA02FE73" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
- Mentum with triangular median tooth; ligula slender and gradually widening towards apex (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A42562CC0FA1AFE4B" box="[1303,1420,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,876,1146]" captionTargetId="figure-497@3.[151,1436,870,1165]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Mentum (ventral view): 2 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 3 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 4 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 5 Schuelea drumonti. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); male sternite 3 with two oval depressions bearing filamentous elongated setae (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A43272CA8FB2EFE73" box="[1126,1208,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,269,1462,1486]" captionTargetBox="[201,1408,184,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-234@8.[151,1436,160,1438]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Median depression and cluster of filamentous setae on 2nd and 3rd sternites of male: 15 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus; 16 Pogonoglossus giganteus; 17 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.; 18 2nd and 3rd sternites of female Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp. Not scaled." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
)..........................3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E4DFB4FFFC647A47D62F70FA03FCB3" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFC647A47D62F70FA03FD13" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFC647A47D62F70FA03FD13" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
3. Antennae longer, extended beyond the base of pronotum by 2–3 antennomeres; dorsal and ventral surfaces of antennomeres 5–11 devoid of impressions at base; antennomeres 2–11 with apical ring of elongate setae; mandibles long, narrow and weakly arcuate; anterior transverse sulcus of pronotum weakly developed; TLA = 7–17.6 (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A45462F08FDCAFD13" box="[519,604,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1306,1330]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,770,1265]" captionTargetId="figure-264@10.[151,1436,764,1282]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Habitus: 23 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.(Holotype); 24 Pogonoglossus giganteus (Holotype); 25 Schuelea drumonti (Holotype); 26 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus (Lectotype). Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108360/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) .................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFFC647A43282F08FA03FD13" authority="Chaudoir." authorityName="Chaudoir." box="[1129,1429,632,658]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A43282F08FA8CFD10" box="[1129,1306,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Pogonoglossus</emphasis>
Chaudoir.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFFC647A47D62FD0FA03FCB3" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<keyLead id="30E16424FFFC647A47D62FD0FA03FCB3" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A47D62FD0FF37FD38" box="[151,161,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">-</emphasis>
Antennae shorter, extended beyond the base of pronotum by only the last; dorsal and ventral surfaces of antennomeres 5–11 bi-impressed at base; antennomeres 2–11 without apical ring of setae; mandibles short, wide and weakly arcuate; anterior transverse sulcus of pronotum very deep; length 
<quantity id="4CE86AF4FFFC647A43B32F80FA0EFC8B" box="[1266,1432,752,778]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.565" metricValueMax="1.68" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="3" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="15.65" valueMax="16.8" valueMin="14.5">14.5–16.8mm</quantity>
. (
<figureCitation id="132BDB94FFFC647A478E2E68FEB2FCB3" box="[207,292,792,818]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1306,1330]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,770,1265]" captionTargetId="figure-264@10.[151,1436,764,1282]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Habitus: 23 Helluodes devagiriensis n.sp.(Holotype); 24 Pogonoglossus giganteus (Holotype); 25 Schuelea drumonti (Holotype); 26 Physocrotaphus ceylonicus (Lectotype). Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5108360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5108360/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) ............................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFFC647A43962E68FA03FCB3" authority="Baehr." authorityName="Baehr." box="[1239,1429,792,818]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Schuelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFFC647A43962E68FAD6FCB0" box="[1239,1344,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="33">Schuelea</emphasis>
Baehr.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
